Anthrax, Armenia
----------------
Information received on [and dated] 23 Oct 2013 from Dr Grisha Baghiyan, 1st Deputy to the Minister, Ministry of Agriculture, Ministry of Agriculture, Yerevan, Armenia.

Summary:
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 4 Oct 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 10 Oct 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: November 2012
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: North West, Hartagyugh, Spitak, Lori
Date of start of the outbreak: 4 Oct 2013
Outbreak status: resolved (20 Oct 2013)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1 / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0
Outbreak statistics (rates apparent, expressed as percentages):
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 100.00 / 0.00 / 0.00 / 100.00
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures:
Measures applied: stamping out; movement control inside the country; zoning; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type: Republican Veterinary and Phytosanitary Center of Laboratory Services (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / agar-gel precipitation (AGP) test / 10 Oct 2013 / Positive
Cattle / Ascoli test / 10 Oct 2013 / Positive
Cattle / bacteriological examination / 10 Oct 2013 / Positive
Cattle / real-time PCR / 10 Oct 2013 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [go to source URL to see map]

